# Applied AI Rig records

This directory is the engineering record for **{{PROJECT_NAME}}**.

## First 15 minutes

The goal is one real decision with enough evidence to review it later. Do not complete every field or
register before the project needs it.

1. Pick a consequential choice you are making now: a model, dataset, evaluation threshold, tool
   permission, operating limit, or fallback.
2. Add it to [Decisions](DECISIONS.md). If the initializer command is installed, preview a skeleton with
   `applied-ai-rig add decision . --id DEC-YYYYMMDD-short-name --title "Describe the choice"` and apply it
   only after review with `--yes`.
3. Put one measured, estimated, or explicitly unknown claim in [Evidence](EVIDENCE.md) and link it to the
   decision. The optional `add evidence` command can create the skeleton.
4. Record only the risk-specific module fields needed to explain that decision. Leave detailed telemetry
   in its canonical tool.
5. Use the [delivery checklist](DELIVERY_CHECKLIST.md) at the next meaningful review or handoff.

Run `applied-ai-rig status .` when the command is available to see structural health, record counts, and
the next useful action. The files remain fully usable by hand when the initializer is not installed.

Read in this order:

1. [Operating principles](OPERATING_PRINCIPLES.md)
2. [Decisions](DECISIONS.md)
3. [Evidence](EVIDENCE.md)
4. [Worklog](WORKLOG.md)
5. [Delivery checklist](DELIVERY_CHECKLIST.md)
